@NODE logfile "Log of all online time/costs"


Every time you quit Oner the total cost and total time
that you were logged on for is written to file.
When ever you want to check , for example , your monthly
costs, you just read this file and count up the session costs.

This file's location and name is specified in the oner.config file.

Note : There is a small bug in that if , for example, you logged
       on at 12:03 and logged off at 13:23 the log file would
       say:-  logon 12:3 and logoff 13:23, as you can see if the
       decimal number is less than ten it does not put a zero in
       front of it. This does not look good but does not effect
       the operation of Oner.
@ENDNODE

@NODE config "Setting up oner for your particular requirements"


An example of the oner.config file :-

   InitCost=0.25
   0100=1
   0200=1.50
   0300=2
   0400=2
   0500=1
   0600=1
   0700=1
   0800=2
   0900=5.75
   1000=9.50
   1100=2.35
   1200=3.00
   1300=1.85
   1400=2.00
   1500=3
   1600=1.15
   1700=5
   1800=6.90
   1900=5
   2000=6
   2100=1.95
   2200=2
   2300=3.50
   0000=1.50
   LogFile=amitcp:log/online.log
   QuitWithAmiTCP=yes


As you can see this example suggests that the user pays $1 per hour
if he is logged on between the hours 0100 and 0200 but pays $2.35 if
he is logged on from 1100 to 1200.

The first line specifies the phone company's call connection cost. 

The second last line specifies the logfile's location and name.

The last line specifies whether Oner quits when AmiTCP quits.

NOTE: the config file must remain the same as is shown here, only the values
      may change. i.e. - it is all case sensitive. You may change the order in
                       which each entry appears in the config file however.
      
      Oner looks for Oner.config in 3 places. (in the following order );

      First it looks for it in the current directory;
      Second it looks for it in S:
      Third it looks for it in AmiTCP:db directory
      
      If it doesn't find it in any of these places it complains or if
      it was run from WorkBench it quits.
      Also note that if you choose the option to quit with AmiTCP, Oner
      will have to be started after AmiTCP in the startnet script.
      put ' run oner '  last in the startnet script and all will be well.
	
@ENDNODE

@NODE history "How this program has changed over time"

V1.0    (May 23 1996) First Aminet release

V1.1    (May 25 1996) Fixed a problem with reading oner.config

V1.2    (May 27 1996) Oner does not wait for AmiTCP to start now 
        (You do not need this if Oner appears near the end of the startnet 
        script.). Changed Oner.guide to be a bit more Multiview friendly.

V1.3	Internal release. Tidied code a bit and made WorkBench window size 
	correctly to the system font. (i.e learned more about Intuition!)
        (Thanks Thorsten.)

V1.4	Oner now includes the initial cost of the call and adds it to the 
	total cost.
        The logfile has changed slightly.
        Changed to a 1200 '030 OS3.0 as my main machine. (at last...) 
@ENDNODE

